# Investment direction policy

When writing or editing `top_investment_implications`:

1. **Prefer Long or Short** tied to the episode thesis — not default Watch.
2. **Max one Watch** per episode (`config/template.yaml` → `investment_policy.watch_max_count: 1`).
3. **Never Watch on tradable tickers** (e.g. DIS, NVDA, BRK.B) — use Long/Short; fold comparative context into thesis.
4. **Never Watch on Private: names** — use Long/Short on the business when cited.
5. **At least one Long or Short** when any tradable ticker is listed (`require_directional_when_tradable: true`).

`src/validate.py` treats violations as **errors**; `publish_approved_batch.py` and `publish_bilingual.py` will block publish.

Framework / methodology episodes still assign Long/Short on example tickers when those tickers appear in implications (e.g. TSM Long after SOP clears), not blanket Watch.

Reference prompts: `prompts/extraction_system.txt`, `prompts/extraction_acquired.txt`.
